<center><a href="/comments/item_comment.shtml?ID=1133">Post a Comment</a>
</center><BR>
<center>
 [ <a href="/armour/individual/lambent_gauntlets.shtml?ID=1133&page=1"> 1 </a> ]</center>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Talanic Scorpse</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-16 11:53:53</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Calm down, it's a lot simpler than it sounds...<BR>
<BR>
Believe it or not, I got my pair of Lambent Gaunts at level 16.  Arguably the stupidest thing I've ever done, but I did it.  I started the quest at level 17, though.<BR>
<BR>
Full Spoiler:<BR>
<BR>
First off, you're right--no griffene charm, that's for bracer. <BR>
<BR>
Black Silk Gloves--off *many* different things in Mistmoore, including the Deathly Usher.  No drop.  Best place to get these is the Secret Room behind the graveyard.  <BR>
<BR>
*special tip:  Almost nothing in Mistmoore can see invis, excepting the Soul Seducer line, which sometimes have a see invis buff up.<BR>
<BR>
While you're there, I suggest also picking up:<BR>
<BR>
Gypsy Lute--this one is kinda harder to get, since the monster that drops it is less often camped.  Inside the castle, first right, first left, under the staircase, right, left, and then you're in the room with the Gypsies. That's the only thing that drops those, but it's worth it for the Lambent BP.  I got mine at level 20, finally, but my friend at level 28 is still lacking his.  No drop.<BR>
<BR>
Also needed:<BR>
Shin Gauntlets--Off Shin Knight in Lower Guk.  Easy to get if you have never killed a froglok because they will not be hostile.  At that point it's a simple matter of waiting for a pair to drop.  Almost nobody loots them because only Bards want them for Lambent Gauntlets.  No drop.<BR>
<BR>
While you're there, I suggest also picking up:<BR>
<BR>
Mask of Deception--you may have to get in line a little, but it's an awesome bard- and rogue-only mask.  No drop.  Off of Ghoul Assassin.<BR>
<BR>
Basalt Carapace--the other item needed for Lambent BP.  No drop.  Off of Basalt Gargoyle.<BR>
<BR>
Shin Greaves--Part of Lambent Greaves quest.  AC of bronze but lighter and resist bonus.  Looks like steel.  No drop.  Off of Shin Knight.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Also needed in the quest is a Lambent Star Ruby.  Two Star Rubies and a Lambent Stone, give it to the NPC indicated in the Temple of Solusek Ro.  Beware--the NPC who talks of lambent stones is not the only one who makes Lambent Gems.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
